description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Registered Mental Health Nurse to join the Community Recovery Service as part of the High Peak and Dales Community Mental Health Team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be part of a multi-disciplinary team and be expected to care coordinate a diverse caseload.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking practitioner who can work on their own initiative, support junior colleagues and is able to communicate with the wider multi-professional team, families and carers and develop links with non-statutory services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also interested in the recruitment of newly qualified nurses .&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate must be able to demonstrate knowledge of all types of mental illness and disorders, risk assessment, have a comprehensive understanding of the CPA process and NICE guidance.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate can expect to work within a friendly, professional, innovative and committed team, receive regular supervision and have training opportunities in order to enhance their career and to meet Revalidation requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Nadine Protheroe Job title: Acting Service Manager Email address: nadine.protheroe@nhs.net Telephone number: 0300 123 3373&lt;/p&gt;
